summary: This is an email exchange between individuals involved in the Epstein case investigation, discussing the status of FBI 302 interview reports and handwritten interview notes. The sender is providing attachments and requesting confirmation on missing materials, indicating a collaborative review process among investigators.
keyFacts: The email discusses the status of over 120 interviews conducted in the Epstein case.
The sender is providing FBI 302 reports and handwritten interview notes, and notes that some interviews were brief and may not have handwritten notes.
The communication indicates a collaborative effort between investigators to cross-reference and complete their collection of interview materials.
